--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INTERNAL GOVERNANCE AGREEMENT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. DECISION MAKING & COMMERCIALIZATION
Future decisions regarding the commercialization, sale, or licensing of this platform must be approved unanimously by all the active copyright holders. No single member or majority may authorize commercial use or transfer rights without the explicit consent of the entire team.

2. REVENUE SHARING
Any net revenue, profits, or proceeds generated from the commercialization or sale of this project shall be distributed equally among the original copyright holders (33.33% each for Diego Andruccioli, Rei Mici, and Giovanni Morelli), unless a different written agreement is unanimously adopted in the future.

3. EXIT CLAUSE & RIGHTS
If a copyright holder voluntarily withdraws from the active project team ("Exiting Member"):
- They retain their right to their equal share of revenue generated by the project.
- They forfeit their right to vote on or veto future business, technical, or commercial decisions. Future decisions will require the unanimous consent of the remaining active members.

4. NON-COMPETE
The copyright holders agree not to use the specific source code, proprietary algorithms, or unique implementation details of this project to create, launch, or contribute to a directly competing platform. This restriction applies while they are part of the team and for a period of 12 months after withdrawing from the project.

